window.bookSummaryJSON = "<p>A millionaire playboy&nbsp;&nbsp;</p> <p>Ben Novack, Jr., was born into a hotel empire, Miami's lavish Fontainbleau. But his luxurious, celebrity-studded lifestyle would ironically end in another hotel room - where the police found him bound up in duct tape, beaten to death.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p> <p>A history of violence&nbsp;&nbsp;</p> <p>Seven years earlier, police found Novack in an eerily similar situation - when his ex-stripper wife Narcy duct-taped him to a chair for 24 hours and robbed him. Claiming it was a sex game, he never pressed charges and never followed through with a divorce.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p> <p>A family murder mystery&nbsp;&nbsp;</p> <p>Prosecutors believed Narcy let the killers into the room and watched them brutalize Novack. They also suspected she was involved in the death of Novack's mother, who took a fatal fall months before. Strangely, it was Narcy's own daughter who implicated her to the police - in this twisted case of passion, perversion, and paradise lost....</p>"; 
